Philippine Stocks: Filinvest Land, Lepanto, Philex Mining

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-04-15T04:55:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/philippine-stocks-filinvest-land-lepanto-philex-mining.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are of at the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index 0.4 percent to 4,251.64,
the highest since Nov. 9. The measure is 3.4 percent below its
record close of 4,397.30 on Nov. 4.  Miners:  Lepanto Consolidated Mining (LC)  Co surged to a
14-year high, leading gains among the nation’s metal producers,
as the price of gold climbed to a record on concern that global
inflation will accelerate, stoking demand for the precious metal.  Lepanto Class A shares, which are reserved for Filipinos,
surged 11 percent to 59 centavos, the highest since March 1997.
Its Class B shares (LCB PM), which have no ownership
restrictions, advanced 8.1 percent to 67 centavos, the highest
since May 1997.  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , the nation’s
biggest miner, gained 1.2 percent to 15.76 pesos.  Filinvest Land Inc. (FLI)  , a property builder, advanced
1.6 percent to 1.26 pesos, the highest since Jan. 14. The
developer said it will pay a 3.92 centavos a share dividend this
year, higher than its 3.3 centavos a share payout in 2010.  To contact the reporter on this story:
